HARRISONBURG â€” Riverheads' Keegan Oliver has qualified for the 1A East Regional golf tournament. 
Oliver shot an 81 last week at the Conference 44 tournament on the Heritage Oaks Golf Course. His score was the third best individual tally from the five teams participating. Richard Gustaffsson was the low medalist with a 4-over-par 74. 
Fellow Gladiator Nick Schroers almost made the regional, but lost in a four-hole playoff. 
"He has been steady all year," Gladiator coach Tim Morris said of Oliver's play. "He is starting to come into his own. I'm looking forward for him to have a successful regional tournament. He has the ability to shoot in the 70s." 
Meanwhile, Luray won the Conference 44 tournament with a 339, two strokes better than second place Altavista's 341. Stonewall Jackson was third with a 371, followed by Riverheads with a 380 and William Campbell with a 390.
